wireguardrtc (0.2.3-1) unstable; urgency=high

  * Release blocker: restore daemon from v0.2.0 corruption.  A
    code-cleanup pass in the v0.2.0 restructure stripped ~80
    trailing `()` from function calls plus three test files'
    indentation; the file remained syntax-valid because each
    corrupted site is a legal bound-method reference (e.g. `main`
    instead of `main()` at module bottom).  Every fresh-install of
    v0.2.0's .deb produced a daemon that exited 0 silently and did
    nothing.  Existing v0.1.0 installs kept working only because
    they were still running the old binary; v0.1.0 -> v0.2.0
    upgrades silently broke.
  * Daemon repair touched ~96 call sites across `wireguardrtc`,
    three test files (`25_parallel_stun.py`, `26_candidate_trim.py`,
    `27_candidate_enumerate.py`), and `fabric.sh`'s nine function
    definitions.  Restored `get_public_ipv4_all`'s missing
    `LOG.event` for the PublicIp override (test 09 caught it).
  * Two CI safeguards added: `tests/28_help_smoke.py` (runs
    `wireguardrtc --help` and fails on empty stdout) and
    `tests/29_ast_lint.py` (flags bare Name/Attribute expressions,
    method refs in boolean contexts, and method-shaped attr
    assignments).
  * Full test pass: 175 daemon assertions + 11 fabric end-to-end
    PASS across the unit and shell/fabric suites.

 -- Markus Gutschke <gutschke@users.noreply.github.com>  Wed, 13 May 2026 12:00:00 +0000

wireguardrtc (0.2.0-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Repository restructured to host the daemon and the Android client
    side by side on a unified version tag.  The daemon source moves
    from the repo root to `daemon/`; behaviour is unchanged.
  * Relicensed from MIT to Apache License 2.0 (the daemon's source
    has no GPL or otherwise-incompatible dependencies; Apache 2.0 was
    chosen for its explicit patent grant).
  * Repo renamed from `wireguardrtc` to `wgrtc` to match the Android
    package id and avoid confusion with the trademarked WireGuard name.

 -- Markus Gutschke <gutschke@users.noreply.github.com>  Mon, 12 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000

